# Documentation Sync Reminder

After making structural changes -- new directories, renamed modules, changed architectural patterns, added/removed major dependencies, or new conventions -- mention to the user that `CLAUDE.md` or `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` files may need updating.

Suggest: "You may want to run the **sync-project-docs** skill to update project documentation."

Do NOT flag routine changes that follow existing documented patterns (new endpoint, new component, new test).
